<HEADLINE>
FT  01 APR 92 / UK Company News: Insurance claim lifts Garton Eng
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
GARTON Engineering lifted pre-tax profits from Pounds 1m to Pounds 1.36m in
1991, helped by exceptional receipts from insurers.
The results were considerably influenced by the continuing effect of the
fire at the end of 1990, Mr Aubrey Garton, chairman, explained. Given the
depressed economic conditions a lower level of profitability would have
occurred.
Turnover fell to Pounds 19.3m (Pounds 22.9m) but the operating surplus moved
up to Pounds 1.59m (Pounds 1.34m). That included Pounds 2.6m net surplus on
replacement of fixed assets and Pounds 1.35m from consequential loss
insurance, and was struck after Pounds 1.3m restructuring and reorganisation
costs.
Earnings per share jumped to 25.84p (17.06p). The dividend is again 7p with
a final of 5.25p.
