<HEADLINE>
FT  01 APR 92 / UK Company News: Hanson sells Beazer to US offshoot
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROLAND RUDD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
HANSON, the Anglo-American conglomerate, last night announced that Beazer,
its wholly-owned subsidiary, has been sold to one of Hanson's US offshoots
as part of the refinancing of Beazer's substantial debt.
Beazer was taken over by Hanson last September, just before it was to float
its UK businesses on the Stock Exchange to enable it to meet obligations to
its banks and make a repayment of Dollars 600m (Pounds 347m) in March 1992.
Beazer's US businesses, which consist of the production of sand, gravel and
aggregates, have now been pledged to Hanson's US banks as security for
Beazer's debt.
In order to do this Beazer has been transferred to the Hanson US subsidiary
for Dollars 91m cash and the assumption of Dollars 100m debt.
Hanson was obliged by the Stock Exchange to announce the move since the
listing of Beazer's 8 per cent convertible unsecured loan stock is to be
maintained.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
