<PROFILE>_AN-CDABOAFGFT</PROFILE>
<DATE>920401
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  01 APR 92 / Observer: Yogi Park
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
If the Maharishi Mahesh Yogi's Natural Law Party fails to win a seat in
Britain's general election, his transcendental meditating supporters can at
least look forward to a break in their very own theme park, soon to be built
 -barring acts of God, presumably  - on the banks of Niagara Falls.
Well-founded reports suggest that the Yogi is teaming up with a Canadian
magician, Doug Henning, to construct a 1,400 acre theme park, costing
CDollars 690m and ready to open in three years' time.
The main promise of the park is to provide 'enlightenment, knowledge and
entertainment', though with a planned 6m visitors annually and an entrance
fee of some Dollars 20, more mercenary motives might be suspected. Today the
House of Commons, tomorrow the White House?
