FT  01 APR 92 / Election 1992: FT election share index
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SHARES that might benefit from a Labour victory suffered one of their
steepest drops of the campaign as the 'Labour gainers' section of the index
slid a full point. Eight of the 10 shares fell and two were unchanged.
'Conservative gainers' did less badly, dropping by only a  1/4 of a point -
a decline that was only half that suffered by the FT-SE index of big-company
stocks.
The FT Election Share index is based on closing prices on March 11, the day
the election was called. Since then Labour gainers have dropped by 2 points,
and Conservative gainers by 6 1/2 points.
