Lines, writes Karen Fossli in Oslo.
The 71,000-ton ship, to be called Imagination, is to be delivered in the
autumn of 1995 and will have capacity for 2,600 passengers.
Mr Erik Toenseth, Kvaerner's president, said yesterday that the new order
brought Kvaerner Masa-Yards' net order book up to an estimated NKr9bn.
Two sister-ships to Imagination, Sensation and Fantasy, are due for delivery
from Masa-Yards respectively in 1993 and 1994. Kvaerner has two Finnish
shipyards, one in Aabo and the other in Helsinki, which combined employ
4,100 people.
</TEXT>
